[ml] Case called at 2:32PM
Defendant Tabitha L Lloyd in court. ADA Krysta Parson appears for the State of Wisconsin.
ADA Parson verifies Victim Rights Compliance.

The Defendant advises that she has completed and submitted a Petition for a County Appointed Attorney shortly before today's hearing. The Court instructs the Clerk to retrieve the Petition so that it may be reviewed by the Court.

----------------------------

After a brief recess, the Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for a County Appointed Attorney, and orders the Defendant to repay the Clerk of Court's Office at a rate of $35.00 a month, starting on or around 07/01/2022 and on or around the first of every month thereafter until the Attorney Fees are paid in full.
The Court continues to toll the Preliminary Hearing time limits.

[MK] case called at 2:00pm 
Defendant Tabitha L Lloyd appears via videoconferencing from the Jefferson County Jail, in custody, along with Public Defender Amber Rumpf  (the PD appears for bond-purposes only; Ms. Lloyd does not qualify for PD representation).  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin. 
The Court finds that the video-connection is sight and sound sufficient. 
Attorney Rumpf provides an updated address for Ms. Lloyd on N. Center Avenue in Jefferson. 
Service of Complaint admitted, reading waived, the charge and maximum penalties are recited.
The Court provides informatoin on right to counsel. The Court directs that the petition form for the appointment of counsel is to be provided to Ms. Lloyd at the Jail.  
The Court schedules the matter for status-of-counsel hearing [The Initial Appearance is adjourned.] 
The Court requires a $1,000 Signature Bond with conditions:
--no contact with Victim 1 or Victim 2 
recess 2:05pm.
